    "collapsible_tabs_ciD8kW": {
      "type": "collapsible-tabs",
      "blocks": {
        "content_Q9xLHk": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What are GVM upgrades, and why are they essential for off-road vehicles?",
            "content": "<p>GVM stands for Gross Vehicle Mass, which is the total weight capacity that your truck can legally carry. GVM upgrades can come from a number of new parts and accessories, but typically are from adding new suspension and improved brakes. </p><p>When you’re heading offroad, you’re typically going to be hauling some major gear - whether that’s in the tray or on a trailer. When you upgrade your GVM, you’ll prevent handling and safety issues and reduce brake wear and tear. It’s essential to ensure you get a safe, enjoyable drive, which means you’re not held back by having to pick and choose which gear to take when you’re roughing it. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_xrHna8": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "How does Offroad Industries’ GVM upgrade service improve your vehicle’s load capacity and performance?",
            "content": "<p>We stock <a href=\"https://www.offroadindustries.com.au/collections/bds-suspension\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">BDS</span></a> and <a href=\"https://www.offroadindustries.com.au/collections/fox-suspension\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">FOX Suspension</span></a>, two manufacturers that deliver some of the highest-quality, resilient and versatile suspension upgrade kits in the market. They offer superior performance, support and durability, boosting your GVM for more hauling power without compromising the integrity or safety of your truck. </p><p>When you’re aiming for a GVM upgrade for trucks and 4x4s, both of these manufacturers will help across the board. You can expect a number of benefits - the key one being the all-important increased load capacity. You’ll also be able to carry larger loads without sacrificing driving comfort or safety, and you’ll get superior offroading performance. Perhaps one of the most important factors is that you’ll legally be able to carry more weight, ensuring you’re operating everything safely for both yourself and other drivers you encounter on and off the road. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_BkcGGW": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "Which vehicle models are eligible for GVM upgrades at Offroad Industries?",
            "content": "<p>Offroad Industries offers GVM upgrade solutions for just about every major 4WD truck in the country. You can find GVM upgrades for everything from Australia’s favourite, the Ford Ranger, to Toyota, Nissan, and Isuzu, along with European and American models like Volkswagen, RAM and Chevrolet. </p><p>For a personal recommendation, you can <a href=\"https://www.offroadindustries.com.au/pages/contact-us\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">contact</span></a> our team. We’ll help you narrow your options down to get the best safety, performance, and GVM upgrade you need. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_Qnr3j6": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What is the step-by-step process for a GVM upgrade with Offroad Industries?",
            "content": "<p>When you’re considering major vehicle transformations, including a GVM upgrade, the team at Offroad Industries work hard to make it as seamless as possible. We’ll consult with you to help you find the best option for your needs, driving preferences, and specific truck make and model. We account for on or off-road usage, and the overall weight you think you’ll need to be hauling. </p><p>Next, you can get everything taken care of by one of our <a href=\"https://www.offroadindustries.com.au/pages/dealers-page\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">authorised installers</span></a>. They’ll ensure everything is completed correctly and deliver the right weight distribution and lift you need from your upgrade. They can also certify that you’ve completed the upgrades, giving you the certification that your vehicle meets Australian Design Rules (ADR) and state-based regulations. <br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_eVHWQQ": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "Are the GVM upgrades provided by Offroad Industries fully compliant with Australian regulations?",
            "content": "<p>Yes, all GVM upgrades from Offroad Industries are fully compliant with Australian Federal and State road safety standards. When your upgrades have been added, they’ll be recorded against your vehicle’s registration information, ensuring you’re fully covered legally when you’re out on the road or on a job site with your truck. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_p66FxM": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "What are the key benefits of upgrading your vehicle’s GVM with Offroad Industries?",
            "content": "<p>There are a lot of benefits to getting offroad GVM upgrades, and they’re not just limited to complying with Australian road legality. You’ll get boosted safety, with the ability to carry or haul heavier loads without sacrificing your truck’s maneuverability. The likes of BDS and Fox Suspension give you superior ride quality and stability, even when you’re heading onto tough terrain. </p><p>Along with the immediately noticeable benefits, you’ll also be investing in the longevity of your truck. GVM upgrades protect the integrity of your brakes and the frame of your vehicle, reducing wear and tear from heavy use. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_CNpm4F": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "How does Offroad Industries ensure the durability and quality of their GVM upgrade solutions?",
            "content": "<p>Our parts and GVM upgrade accessories are all torture-tested by the manufacturers that design them. We stock aftermarket parts specifically designed to fit your truck’s dimensions, and they’re all made from high-quality materials with the toughest conditions in mind. They go through rigorous testing, ensuring the best quality and safety is guaranteed. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_GMT6pr": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "4WD GVM Upgrades – Enhance Your Towing and Off-Road Capabilities",
            "content": "<p>No matter what you drive, if you’re heading off the beaten track or need a rugged vehicle for work, chances are you need some serious hauling capabilities. Every kilo matters and GVM upgrades not only give you that extra payload, but also make sure the structure of your vehicle stays in top shape. Whether you’re taking a caravan out to the coast for the weekend, need a winch to do work out on a farm, or just want to load up the tub with all your camping gear, you’ll want to consider professionally engineered 4WD GVM upgrades. <br/>Here at Offroad Industries, we have a range of options for all of Australia’s most popular vehicles. From Ford F150s and Toyota Landcruisers to American-made trucks like Chevy Silverado, we’ve engineered everything to give you the towing and carrying capabilities you want without sacrificing handling when you’re offroading. <br/></p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_HpDB4n": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "4x4 GVM Upgrades – Improve Your Vehicle’s Load Capacity",
            "content": "<p>When you first drive your truck off the lot, it’ll come with a factory standard manufacturer-rated load limit, referred to as Gross Vehicle Mass. This number varies depending on the make and model, but the figure includes its maximum weight while still being able to operate. It includes the weight of your passengers, fuel, accessories and cargo combined. As soon as you’re adding extra gear or something heavy-duty to the trailer, it doesn’t take much to exceed that number. </p><p>If you want to tap into the real potential of your truck, a GVM upgrade that’s made with top quality aftermarket parts is essential. It boosts that number significantly, with some Stages giving you anywhere up to more than a 100% increase in payload. </p><p>It takes a special combination of new suspension, which also gives you greater ground clearance, as well as coils and leaf packs to give you the same power and control, while seriously amping up the weight you can handle.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_hJL8Az": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "GVM Upgrades for 4WD and 4x4 Vehicles in Australia",
            "content": "<p>No matter where you live, there’s no doubt that Australia’s climate and conditions are rugged and demand the most from you and your vehicle, especially when you’re offroading. From touring through arid environments in WA to the humid and muddy terrain in Victoria, when you’re navigating, you need all the traction and control you can get, especially when you’re taking heavy duty gear with you. </p><p>GVM upgrades are engineered and certified solutions that make it possible to safely and legally carry more weight than the original manufacturer rating. That means you can venture off the road, take everything you need, and still feel comfortable, safe, and capable even when you’re loaded up. For Australian drivers building a capable touring or working setup, upgrading the payload with 4WD GVM upgrades is often one of the most transformational things you can do to get more from every drive and truly maximise your truck’s potential.</p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        },
        "content_UMaFLU": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "none",
            "title": "GVM Upgrades for 4WDs and 4x4s – Maximum Load Capacity and Performance",
            "content": "<p>If you’ve ever added a few kilos extra to your truck than you really should, you’ll know how much it can make your vehicle feel like it’s sinking into the suspension. You’d also notice how much more care you need when navigating, as the extra weight can throw off your truck’s balance and braking capabilities. </p><p>If you demand more, and want to load up everything without worry, a dedicated, tested, and properly engineered GVM upgrade from Offroad Industries will give you what you need. You can unlock the ability to carry the gear you actually want for work or adventure without compromising safety. </p><p>At Offroad Industries, we focus on building 4WDs that are engineered to perform no matter the reason for your journey. From heavy-duty and resilient suspension upgrades to rugged control arms,, our GVM upgrades help ensure your vehicle is ready for towing, touring and tackling Australia’s toughest terrain. </p>",
            "custom_liquid": "",
            "content_page": "",
            "open": false
          }
        }
      },
